name: Community Vaccination Center at Bellingham Technical College
address: Bellingham Technical College, 3028 Lindbergh Avenue – Building G, Bellingham WA, 98225
info:
College Days One and Done (Janssen) Clinic!  Be prepared for the fall semester vaccination requirement with a single vaccination visit.  All adults 18 and over are welcome to register and attend - first come first served.  Walk-ins are welcome.

If you are having difficulty signing up via the web-site, or need additional assistance, please call our Vaccine Access Scheduler Line at 360-778-6075 on Monday through Friday from 8:30 AM to 4:00 PM.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info: ***1ST & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Post Office Park which is across the street from the Post Office in Toppenish. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98512
info: This is a Johnson & Johnson mobile clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm-8pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
